      • getByName

        public JavaClassModel getByName​(String qualifiedName)
                         throws NonUniqueResultException
        Find a JavaClassModel by the qualified name, returning a single result. If more than one result is available, a AmbiguousJavaClassModel reference will be returned.
        Throws:
        NonUniqueResultException

      • create

        public JavaClassModel create​(String qualifiedName)
        Indicates that we have found a .class or .java file for the given qualified name. This will either create a new JavaClassModel or convert an existing PhantomJavaClassModel if one exists.

      • getOrCreatePhantom

        public JavaClassModel getOrCreatePhantom​(String qualifiedName)
        Gets an existing JavaClassModel, however if none currently exists, then create a PhantomJavaClassModel.

        This is intended to indicate that we know about a class by reference (for example another class subclasses it, or it is referenced in an XML file), but we do not yet have a location on the disk for the class (or source) file itself.

        To create a class (possibly converting a PhantomJavaClassModel to concrete in the process), use create(String) instead.
